  "text_preview": "ASL roommate ASL Lessons | Bookstore | Library | ASL University Main ► American Sign Language: \"roommate\" ROOMMATE, \"companion,\" or \"partner.\" If you do the sign \"COMBINE\"-(match) using a double movement it can mean changes to mean \"roommate\" or \"companion.\" Bring the hands together twice. The fingers are each bent at the two smaller knuckles. Sentence: \"Do you prefer to live alone or with a roommate?\" YOU PREFER LIVE SINGLE-[alone] [bodyshift \"or\"] ROOMMATE-[match] WHICH? Also see: MATCH * Want to help support ASL University? It's easy : DONATE ( Thanks! ) * Another way to help is to buy something from Dr. Bill's \" Bookstore .\" * Want even more ASL resources? Visit the \" ASL Training Center ! \" (Subscription Extension of ASLU) * Also check out Dr. Bill's channel: www.youtube.com/billvicar"
}
